## Lesson Metadata

3. Proposed Lesson Title: Obtaining and Sending transcripts
4. Lesson Abstract (3-4 sentences):

This tutorial will guide students how to obtain and distribute official and unofficial transcripts. Additionally, give resources for uncommon issues and solutions. 

5. A short description of the situation/need that your lesson responds to (consider details of purpose, audience, context):

Students of junior colleges often intend to transfer to universities. A student may want to apply to a specific program with specific prerequisite course. Some universities will evaluate your unofficial transcript before the student applies to the university. In order to apply to a university students must send official transcripts to the receiving university all transcripts from colleges theyâ€™ve attended.

6. Learning Outcomes of Tutorial (between 2-3):

After completing this tutorial students:

* will be able to sign into MyPierce and Parchment.
* will be able to obtain an unofficial transcript.
* will be able to send or receive an official transcript.
7. Course most relevant to your tutorial (if any): English 101 or any course that asks students to compose with sound.

8. Discipline/Research Area most relevant to your tutorial? Example - Humanities / Social Sciences / Mathematics / Natural Sciences / Physical Sciences / Business-Pro-Tech / other

This tutorial is relevant to multiple disciplines/ all students.

9. Intended Submission Date:

I'll have an initial draft of this complete by Friday, Jan. 31. Final version by Feb. 5

10. Lesson will use open technology and data at no cost to the reader?

Both, there is a fee to order official transcripts. However, it is free to view unofficial transcripts.

11. Any other comments for the editor?

